examples.korean: I think it’s time we tried a fresh approach. 발음듣기 내 생각에는 우리가 새로운 방법을 써야 할 때인 것 같다. Oxford Advanced Learner's English-Korean Dictionary
examples.english: I think it’s time we tried a fresh approach. 발음

examples.korean: I’ve been a heavy smoker for over 10 years, but I think it’s time to finally kick the habit. 발음듣기 10년 넘게 골초였는데, 드디어 습관을 끊어야 할 때인 것 같아. DARAKWON
examples.english: I’ve been a heavy smoker for over 10 years, but I think it’s time to finally kick the habit. 발음

examples.korean: Well, spring sprang. We've had our state of grace and our little gift of sanctioned madness, courtesy of Mother Nature. Thanks, Gaia. Much obliged. I guess it's time to get back to that daily routine of living we like to call normal. (David Assael) 발음듣기 봄이 왔구려. 우리는 은총을 받았고, 자연이 베풀어준 허가된 광기라는 작은 선물도 받은 것이요. 고맙소, 대지의 여신이여. 참으로 감사하오. 이제 우리가 정상이라고 부르는 일상의 삶으로 돌아갈 때인듯 하오. (데이비드 아셀, 계절명언) 명언/속담
examples.english: Well, spring sprang. We've had our state of grace and our little gift of sanctioned madness, courtesy of Mother Nature. Thanks, Gaia. Much obliged. I guess it's time to get back to that daily routine of living we like to call normal. (David Assael) 발음
